document_data.Abilities:
[[File:Belvyre the Cat.png|thumb|right|300px|''As Amos astutely observed, Belvyre was not usually a cat. Sometimes, however, he was.'']]
Belvyre was an avid herbalist and botanist, and spent all his time studying myriad variety of plant life. He had a magnificent underground greenhouse where he could safely cultivate his plants in an environment safe from the frigid climate of the [[Frozenfar]].

He had the adorable ability of transforming into a [[cat|house cat]].{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 3|17}}

document_data.History:
[[File:Belvyre_and_Patience_2.png|thumb|left|350px|''Patience saved Belvyre's life on countless occasions&hellip;'']]
When the [[Everlasting Rime]] struck Icewind Dale in the {{YearlinkName|1492}}, Belvyre was hired by the council of the Ten Towns to help preserve and regrow the dying plants within their food stores. While Belvyre was working on a solution for the dying plant life, he was introduced by his friend Saarvin to two other companions investigating the Everlasting Rime, the [[barbarian]] named [[Runa]] and a mysterious [[warlock]] called [[Amos]]. During their first meeting, Amos suggested they journey to an underground cavern that led to a [[Ythryn|magical city]] that was buried deep beneath the [[Reghed Glacier]].

The group set out across Icewind Dale for the glacier, and were eventually forced to take refuge in a cave to keep safe from the elements.{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 2|10-17}} He took Belvyre to an underground cavern full of sacred winter plants, which were nourished by the magic of a ''[[primordial shard]]''. After sharing how he planned to exploit Belvyre's talents, Amos took him to [[Xardorok Sunblight|the master]] of the ''primordial shard'' army.{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 3|6-10}}{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 4|7}}

[[File:Belvyre_and_Patience.png|thumb|right|350px|''&hellip;and Belvyre finally got a chance to return the favor.'']]
As Belvyre's friends delved into the caverns Amos had taken Belvyre,{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 3|19-20}} Amos' master decided to use the ''primordial shard'' to trigger an underground volcanic eruption to destroy them. As his companions arrive to save him, Belvyre confronted Amos and urged him help save the [[duergar]] that would be inadvertently killed by the imminent disaster. He urged his freinds to spare Amos' life and protected him from their vengeance.{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 4|8-14}} As lava burst forth from the depths of the cavern, and the ground shook beneath them, Amos gave the ''frostbrand'' to Belvyre so he could save himself, their companions, and the unwary duergar. Belvyre managed to save Patience's life for once. Working together, the companions escaped to safety and stood poised ready to uncover the secrets of the long lost magical city.{{Cite comic/At the Spine of the World 4|15-19}}
